    "### What is multi-threading? "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5470ec15-f7fa-48b8-8b06-fc64bc35f3b6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Multithreading is a programming technique that allows concurrent execution of multiple threads within a single process."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f5af3409-06ea-4dff-a2c5-dd3d664bcb59",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### Threads are lightweight processes that share the same memory space.\n",
    "##### Python's 'threading' module provides a way to create and manage threads.\n",
    "##### Example: Using threading to perform I/O operations while keeping the main program responsive.\n",
    "##### Multithreading can improve performance in I/O-bound tasks but may not significantly speed up CPU-bound tasks due to the Global Interpreter Lock (GIL).\n",
    "##### Example: A web server handling multiple requests simultaneously using threads.\n"
   ]
  },
