    "What are the OOPS concepts\n",
    "\n",
    "Object-oriented programming concepts that focus on classes and objects.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Encapsulation: Bundling data and methods that operate on the data into a single unit (class).\n",
    "\n",
    "    Inheritance: Ability of a class to inherit properties and behavior from another class.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Polymorphism: Ability to present the same interface for different data types.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Abstraction: Hiding the complex implementation details and showing only the necessary features.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "| Pillar        | Purpose                                                   |\n",
    "| ------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |\n",
    "| Encapsulation | Bundle data + methods; hide internal details              |\n",
    "| Abstraction   | Hide complex details; expose only necessary parts         |\n",
    "| Inheritance   | Reuse code; create class hierarchies                      |\n",
    "| Polymorphism  | Same interface, different behaviors                       |"
   ]
