    "\n",
    " ####   What is method overriding?\n",
    "\n",
    "        When a child class redefines a method from the parent class with the same name.\n",
    "\n",
    "  ####  What is multiple inheritance?\n",
    "\n",
    "        A class inherits from more than one parent class:\n",
    "        class Child(Parent1, Parent2):.\n",
    "\n",
    "   ####  What is super()?\n",
    "\n",
    "        Calls the parent class's methods (often in __init__ to initialize parent attributes).\n",
    "\n",
    "  #### What are @staticmethod and @classmethod?\n",
    "\n",
    "        @staticmethod: Doesn't access instance or class data; just a utility function.\n",
    "\n",
    "        @classmethod: Receives cls (class) as first argument; can modify class-level data."
